modal-rust-sdk
==============

This crate (`modal-rust-sdk`, lib `modal_rust_sdk`) is a first-party Rust gRPC
client for Modal's control plane. It is licensed under "MIT OR Apache-2.0".

It does NOT depend on either project listed below at build time or run time.
Both are read-only references used only during development. The items credited
here are the vendored proto file and the implementation patterns it follows.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
modal-client — the official Modal Python SDK
  https://github.com/modal-labs/modal-client
  License: Apache-2.0 / MIT

  - proto/api.proto is copied VERBATIM from modal-client's
    modal_proto/api.proto (the canonical Modal API definition,
    `package modal.client`). It is vendored, not referenced.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
modal-rs — the unofficial Rust SDK for Modal
  https://github.com/thehumanworks/modal-rs
  License: MIT

  - The build-script recipe (tonic-prost-build + protoc-bin-vendored), the
    auth / channel / interceptor structure, and the CBOR (args, kwargs) codec
    follow modal-rs as the closest Rust precedent.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
